# Validation Generation

This rule helps us create validations for General Transit Feed Specification files. 

## Purpose

- The goal is to create a validation rule given a README.md
- For each validation there will also be a unit tests associated with it.

## Coding Rules
- You will write clean and performant code.
- Speed is a top priority
- Provide comments explaining what each section does.
- Do not create any new type files. If you need modify [gtfs.go](mdc:validator/types/gtfs.go).

- Types:
    - Optional values should be pointers
    - Required values should not be pointers
    - Enum values should be pointers
    - Enums are optional when specified in the "Presence" column in the README.md or when empty is an option as described in the "Description" column

## Resource Files
- Types: [gtfs.go](mdc:validator/types/gtfs.go)
- Utils: [utils.go](mdc:validator/lib/utils.go)
- Validator Functions:[validators.go](mdc:validator/lib/validators.go)

## Example

**IMPORTANT: YOU SHOULD FOLLOW THIS EXAMPLE WHEN APPLYING THIS RULE**

- Markdown Example: [README.md](mdc:validator/validations/stops/README.md) 
- Validation Rule: [parse_trips.go](mdc:validator/validations/trips/parse_trips.go)  
- Unit Test: [parse_trips_test.go](mdc:validator/validations/trips/parse_trips_test.go)   
  

### How to convert values:

```go
// Convert Optional Primitive Values
var bikesAllowed int
lib.ParseStringToPrimitive(m["bikes_allowed"], &bikesAllowed, &parsingErrors)
trip.BikesAllowed = lib.IfThenElse(m["bikes_allowed"] != "", &bikesAllowed, nil)

// Convert Required Values
lib.ParseStringToPrimitive(m["trip_id"], &trip.TripId, &parsingErrors)

// Convert Required Enum Values
var paymentMethod int
lib.ParseStringToPrimitive(m["payment_method"], &paymentMethod, &parsingErrors)
trip.BikesAllowed = lib.IfThenElse(m["payment_method"] != "", &paymentMethod, nil)
```

### Error Handling

Instead of throwing an error, we should append the error to the a list of errors.

```go
var parsingErrors []string

lib.ParseStringToPrimitive(m["trip_id"], &trip.TripId, &parsingErrors)

if len(parsingErrors) > 0 {
    for _, err := range parsingErrors {
        messages = append(messages, types.Message{
            Field:   "N/A", //TODO: Add field name
            Message: err,
        })
    }
}

// Validate Values According to the README.md
// Validate Required trip_id
if trip.TripId == "" {
    messages = append(messages, types.Message{
        Field:   "trip_id",
        Message: "Trip ID is required and must be unique.",
    })
}
```


